				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have played many character classes and races, and i have enjoyed most of them, but smib the cleric is by far my favorite.  Unlike my pure caster characters, smib never meds, maybe he meditates once every 10th kill.  The reason is simple, I have an incredibly high wisdom.  I was able to get this high wisdom because I roleplay.  When i am on the boat, i roleplay and sometimes that roleplaying amuses high powered guys, and they give me a nice piece of jewelry or some such thing.  Besides being fun to play and powerful (maybe we dont hit hard, but then again when smib is in a party, the party never dies!)  Smib has found friends throughout the lands of norrath, and never has any problems finding other friends.  Here is my simple advise:  roleplay, EQ is a roleplaying game, do not forget that!.  put many points into wisdom when ye are starting a cleric, because the more wisdom ye have, the more mana ye have, the more spells ye can cast.  also, if at all possible use a 1handed blunt weapon and a dolly, My dolly named jack helps me many times by giving me more mana,  sure ye wont do many dmg with a 1handed weapon, but then again nearly every class will be out damaging ye anyhow.  and lastly, if ye are in a large group, feel free to stard back and keep everyone at full health, trust me, most of the time your healing will be more helpful to the group than just bashing.
				</font>
