	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I love being a Cleric.  In real life I enjoy helping people, so being a Cleric was and easy fit for me.  I'm very close to lev 14, a lev of great spells.  I looking forward to bind, our group will be off traveling around the world.  When I say group, I mainly mean a Bard and myself.  I love groups of all sizes, but with two or three you have a lot more mana for DD spells.  I keep them (or him) buffed at all times.  About buffing, no matter how large your group is space your buffs out.  I buff then mediate back to Fm and wait a few mins then buff the next guy.  During a battle or between spawns you do not want to buff three people in a roll, because you will find yourself very low on mana.  A low mana or Oom cleric is not much use.<BR>
I keep a close eye on the life of other members and only heal based on the amt. of damage they are taking, then only heal to keep them safe.  Never heal all the way even after the fight is over.  Based on the amt. of mana I will heal them up to 75-80% health.  They while I meditate they can sit, that way by the time I'm Fm they will be full health.  I always try to time Fm with full health for me and all group members.<BR>
<BR>
I love small groups (2-3) with these size groups you can use more DD spells and still be the most praised Cleric of the land.  I love also having a Bard in my group, these guys songs help save a lot of mana.  I stay near Fm all the time with the Bard around.<BR>
<BR>
About groups I got in a group at level 8 and have not looked back since.  I hate playing solo.  I have never died in a good group, but I have died many, many times when I was all alone.  <BR>
Yes, the blues do hit hard, even a lev 14.  When I'm alone and fighting a con black/white or yellow I have to use DD spells with melee just to stay alive, but against the undead that's a different story.<BR>
<BR>
Money, glad you asked.  At lev 8 I left FP and went to Steamfont mts and in a group fought earth elements, young drakes, etc.  They gave good exp., but bad loot, and knowing I need 50pp for lev 14 spells me and the group went to the Bandit camps in lfaydark.  Bandits are good exp. (lev 11-14) and very good loot.  I have made 30pp in cash and have sooo much bronze in the bank I will have no problem buying the lev 14 goodies.  We have to find good exp. with good loot.  You have to talk to people learn where to hunt.<BR>
<BR>
Helping people out -- if you do not like to help, do not be a Cleric!!!!  I always look for people to help out.  If I'm in a group they are naturally first, but even then between spawns and I'm Fm I will still help people out.  At level 12 I was talking to lev 16, and if was sitting near a guard (which means he just got but his kicked).  I talked to him and healed him and buffed him all I could, and ask could I come along to help, he said no due to the fact what he was fighting, if he died could kill me quickly.  He left and I medded to Fm and went on my way, then I found him fighting and his life was below 50%, so from a safe distance I stared healing and meding to keep my mana up and keep him alive.  He won and was so thankful he gave me 5pp, I told him it was not necessary, but he insisted and I was thankful.  He will help me if close whenever I call.  I do enjoy helping people.  <BR>
<BR>
Later fellow Clerics, if you see me say Hail... :)<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
