	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				You will not regret playing a cleric.  That comment about hi-level clerics being too common, and, therefore, it will be hard to get a party - WRONG!  I am a Lvl 34 cleric and I am swamped with requests to party within a minute or two of loggin on.  You are the indispensable party member.  <BR>
One point, however, if you really want to have fun and be respected and loved in your role, PLAY YOUR CLASS. Sure, I can do several hundred damage with my DD spells, but it is nothing compared to the true nukers.  And your fighters, given time and healing, will wear ANYTHING down.  So, why are you indispensable and loved in a party?<BR>
To truly be respected and sought after you must paly your role - you are a healer.  Your party's health, safety, and effectiveness are your concern.  When you join a party, put your best buffs on each and every party member.  This will ultimately add hundreds of HP to EACH paryt member and, believe me that is appreciated. If appropriate, place protective spells on each member, like Endure Magic or Poison or whatever.  Do it when you join and keep those buffs up.<BR>
Then HEAL.  Carefully gauge how many HP your healing spell can do max, and then hit your players with that heal as soon as they lose that many points.  One exception to this.  I carry a big heal spell and the next lower one as well.  I heal the magic user's as soon as they lose the max HP that the LESSER spell will heal.  You need to keep them up to max HP -- they will appreciate it a lot! And they can die on you quickly if you wait.<BR>
Finally, don't be afraid to med during a fight.  Once you pass level 25 your weapon damage is trivial compared to your fighter's.  So, med up so the party can keep fighting.  If you get ahead of the game, rebuff or cast those DD spells.  I see so many clerics in there pinging away in melee and then yelling &quot;OOM&quot; later in the fight as their fighters start yelling for heals. Ridiculous!<BR>
If you follow these precepts, it won't be the grand nuker that will get the hearty hails and hugs, it won't be the fighter that gets the compiments... It will be YOU, the provider and protector of your party!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
