	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				*yawn* I don't really want to discuss the whole boring/not boring issue, but I feel that I must. Let me just say that there's nothing greater than the thrill of knowing that YOU'RE the one that is<BR>
keeping your group alive.  While this takes a LOT of practice (knowing when and why to use mana, when to attack etc) it is COMPLETELY worth it. I've played other classes and I just don't get the<BR>
same rush, and all you players who AREN'T Clerics can't deny how relieved you are when you're being smacked around, are at 1/2 a bubble of health and<BR>
then become miraculously saved by our heal spells.<BR>
<BR>
One thing you have to be careful of, is casting too many heals too soon. Healing party members is just like doing damage to the monster/whatever you're fighting, if you cast too much, you'll be getting hammered by everything and you'll be <BR>
SCREAMING &quot;GET 'EM OFF ME&quot; and hoping your tanks have a good TAUNT rating.<BR>
<BR>
Another not so nice, yet pleasing aspect of the Cleric is, well, watching people die.  This isn't a good idea to to with great frequency, however, you've all grouped with that @$#%%$# who does<BR>
nothing but take all the loot and who couldn't care less about the rest of the group....ANYWAY, after you've taken about as much as you can, you just simply stop healing, say &quot;I'm out of mana, oh crap!&quot; or something, and watch them die.  You'll be feeling better in no time.<BR>
<BR>
ROOT and SMITE will be your best friends for a long while.  So will the spell that causes blindness if you're +pvp or in a duel.  It's so funny to watch people run around aimlessly, while<BR>
you a)med b)wail on them c)cast on them or d)run away as fast as you can.<BR>
<BR>
HAMMER OF WRATH is nice because it gives you a magical melee ability early on, only monks get it as early or earlier.<BR>
<BR>
SUMMON FOOD AND DRINK are nice too, but irritating You'll be poor most of the time, as you'll have to pay for armor and weapons AND spells.  I suggest<BR>
getting a fine steel morningstar as early as you can, to go with the hammer of wrath.<BR>
<BR>
Soloing is an option, but if you aren't doing undead you'll have to be careful after 16 or so depending on where you are, and combat will get mind-numbingly boring.  You wont hit for much, and<BR>
wont get hit for much, so combat will take FOREVER at times, no dual wield or double attack sucks. You'll be able to go afk in the middle of a fight.<BR>
<BR>
Overall, being a cleric is a lot of fun, but it has its drawbacks, the games designers seem to overlook it, no class specific stuff that I know of, cool quests etc, you're POOR, I can't stress<BR>
this enough, especially since they continually change the high loot areas, you'll be reduced to healing and fighting undead a lot of the time.<BR>
<BR>
But your direct damage spells will be better than a magicians at times, you'll be able to solo stuff easier that others of your level if you know what you're doing, and you'll be worshipped by those<BR>
whose lives you save.<BR>
<BR>
The only thing that TRULY irritates me is the fact that some Shaman and Druids will continually tell you that they can heal as well as you can, which is essentially the same as an enchanter telling a wizard that his direct damage spells are just as good, or a rogue or bard telling a warrior that they're equals in hand to hand combat.<BR>
<BR>
My last comment will be simply this:<BR>
<BR>
Halflings kick ass.  Never underestimate the short guy with big feet.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
