	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'd like to add my voice to the &quot;anti-boring&quot; group. Especailly when you get into the high teen levels you learn to use techniques that keep a whole group alive juggling mana and health, and making the crucial judgment on whether or not to use mana for a offensive spell at a critical time in the mele. <BR>
<BR>
I think too that to enjoy being a cleric and finding it exciting, you have to care about the people you group with. If you are just there to power game to get loot, its not for you. If you care a lot about the people you are with, even<BR>
if you just met them, its a fun challenge to do everything in your power to keep your new friends alive in a nasty mele. 
				</font>
			</td>

